McMellon supposedly slipped and fell as he and the other officers confronted Diallo.
Bronx District Attorney Robert Johnson plans to meet with theDiallos shortly before 2 p.m., when the grand jury indictments arescheduled to be unsealed in open court.
The Diallo case has spawned three official investigations _ bythe US Justice Department, federal prosecutors, and the New Yorkstate attorney general _ into a possible pattern of racialdiscrimination in the department's practices.
``Ideally, the physical evidence should support oneconclusion,'' said Peter R. De Forest, a professor at John JayCollege of Criminal Justice.
